{
  "texts": [
    "Due to the close relationship between hyperbolic space, hierarchies, and trees, several works have explored hierarchical clustering using hyperbolic space.",
    "Monath et al. (2019) propose to perform hierarchical clustering using hyperbolic representations.",
    "Given a dataset D = {x i } N i=1, Monath et al. (2019) require a hyperbolic representation at the edge of the Poincaré disk D d for each data point x i ∈ D, which becomes the leaves of the hierarchical clustering.",
    "The method of Monath et al. (2019) creates a hierarchical clustering by optimizing the hyperbolic representations for a fixed number of internal nodes.",
    "Parent-children dissimilarity between a child representation z c and a parent representation z p is measured by"
  ]
}